author: Timothy Puko
title: Natural Gas Gains as Traders Ready for Storage Update
text:
Natural gas prices posted small gains on Thursday in trading sharply limited by an upcoming storage update.
Natural gas for October delivery was up 2.4 cents, or 0.9%, at $2.672 a million British thermal units on the New York Mercantile Exchange. Prices have stayed within a 4.4-cent range Thursday morning, a time when trading and volatility are often low ahead of the U.S. Energy Information Administrationâ€™s weekly update on gas...
